dcterms:description: CCTA images provide clinicians with a detailed view of the heart and its blood vessels, enabling the identification of CHD-related conditions such as atherosclerosis, stenosis, and blockage. The segmentation process partitions the CCTA image into distinct segments, each representing a different anatomical structure.
dcterms:title: CCTA (Coronary Computed Tomography Angiography) images
